clinical_study.brief_title: Dehydration of Stenfilcon A Contact Lenses Versus Delefilcon A Contact Lenses
clinical_study.official_title: Dehydration of Stenfilcon A Contact Lenses Versus Delefilcon A Contact Lenses

brief_summary.textblock: The study will explore in vivo lens dehydration rates across a 12hr wear period for the study lenses.

detailed_description.textblock: The study will explore in vivo lens dehydration rates across a 12hr wear period for the study lenses. The primary outcome variable for this study is the loss in lens weight over the day, which will indicate the amount of dehydration that has occured.

primary_outcome.measure: Absolute Change in Water Content (Mean) of Stenfilcon A and Delefilcon A
primary_outcome.description: Comparison between lens types up to and at 12 hours of wear for the absolute change in water content (WC).

primary_outcome.description: Comparison between lens types up to and at 12 hours of wear for the absolute change in water content (WC).

primary_outcome.measure: Moisture Retention (Mean) of Stenfilcon A and Delefilcon A
primary_outcome.description: Comparison between lens types up to and at 12 hours of wear of moisture retention by measuring relative percentage dehydration (RPD).

primary_outcome.description: Comparison between lens types up to and at 12 hours of wear of moisture retention by measuring relative percentage dehydration (RPD).

secondary_outcome.description: Subjective ratings for stenfilcon A and delefilcon A assessed at every hour up to 12 hours. (Scale 0-100, 0=very poor 100=excellent)

outcome.title: Absolute Change in Water Content (Mean) of Stenfilcon A and Delefilcon A
outcome.description: Comparison between lens types up to and at 12 hours of wear for the absolute change in water content (WC).
outcome.population: There were outliers across four participants in five lenses due to the fact that the weight of the worn lens after 12 hours was greater than the baseline weight of the lens from the blister pack. The sample size for statistical analysis is reduced to 18 pairs.
